description:
The Police Around the World

Arts Documentary with no narration published by A&amp;M in 1982 - English language


Information
------------------------------

In 1980 and 1981 the Police went on a tour which took them through more than a dozen countries. This film features highlights of that tour which included stops in Japan, Hong Kong, India, Egypt, Australia and Latin America. Recorded live during the tour are 16 songs featured on this film : Next To You; Light Changes; Walking On The Moon; Born in the 50's; So Lonely; Man In A Suitcase; Can't Stand Losing You; Bring On The Night; Canary In A Coalmine; Driven To Tears; When The World Is Running Down; Shadows In The Rain; De Do Do Do, De Da Da Da; Don't Stand So Close To Me; Truth Hits Everybody; Roxanne; Message In A Bottle. 
However, this is more than video rock concert - there are many humorous off-stage shots that highlight this film of the band sampling some of the sights, customs and culture of the lands their fans call home.

